<p>
	 Transpose of a Matrix
</p>
<p>
	For computational purposes sometimes we need to switch the order of a matrix, so instead of  working with a <m>2 \times 3</m> matrix we can make computations with a <m>3\times 2</m> matrix. This operation is called <term>the transpose</term> of a matrix, and it works by transforming the rows of the given matrix into columns for the transpose. Here is an example:
</p>

